<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-82-0532 </DOCNO><TEXT>A general description, based primarily on a survey of relevant literature,of both the present global situation regarding climatic changes causedby the greenhouse effect' and the historical background for this phenomenum.Specific environmental effects are briefly explained, and possible strategiesfor mitigating them, especially in relation to Denmarks energy and environmentalpolicy, are discussed. Emphasis is laid on the significance of escalatingglobal consumption of energy with resulting increase of carbon dioxideemission. (AB) 204 refs.</TEXT></DOC>